	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>336 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&quot;it's not like the 2 hp regen of AoB could do anything against a 300ish hitter mob :D (and i wonder if AoB stacks with avatar...)&quot;<br><br>2HP regen comes in handy in a raid situation and the mob AoEs.&nbsp;&nbsp;If an encounter lasted, say, 10 minutes, that is 200 HP of regen.  That is probably greater than the benefit received from an additional 15 STA (which, oh by the way, is NOT *easy* to max out and I know not why people constantly say it is).  This is to say nothing about the increase to attack (which is more like 14 at 65, not 10).<br><br>AoB, IF it is a triggered buff, like Pauldrons of Ferocity, does NOT stack with avatar.  However, BoDS, Vindy BP, and other *permanent* AoB items DO stack with avatar.<br><br>Luna</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
